President Obama spoke with President Hollande of France about the situation in Iraq. They agreed that there is a need for an urgent and coordinated international response to the humanitarian crisis on Mount Sinjar. They also discussed the threat that the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL) poses to all Iraqi communities and the need to support Iraq in countering these extremists. They also talked about the targeted strikes that the United States is conducting to protect U.S. personnel and prevent ISIL's advance on Erbil. They agreed to work together on a longer term strategy to counter ISIL.